    normalize = lambda x: (x - np.mean(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True)) / np.std(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True)
# h5_files = glob("data/*.h5")
# for file in h5_files:
file = f"data/{event_id}.h5"
with h5py.File(file, "r") as fp:
    ds = fp["data"]
    data = ds[...]
    dt = ds.attrs["dt_s"]
    dx = ds.attrs["dx_m"]
    nx, nt = data.shape
    x = np.arange(nx) * dx
    t = np.arange(nt) * dt
        
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(normalize(data).T, cmap="seismic", vmin=-1, vmax=1, aspect="auto", extent=[x[0], x[-1], t[-1], t[0]], interpolation="none")
plt.xlabel("Distance (m)")
plt.ylabel("Time (s)")

    Copied! 
    normalize = lambda x: (x - np.mean(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True)) / np.std(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True)
with h5py.File(f"data/{filename.split('/')[-1]}", "r") as fp:

    dx = fp["Acquisition"].attrs["SpatialSamplingInterval"]
    fs = fp['Acquisition/Raw[0]'].attrs["OutputDataRate"]
    dt = 1.0 / fs
    data = fp["Acquisition/Raw[0]/RawData"][...]
    data = np.gradient(data, axis=-1) / dt

    nx, nt = data.shape
    x = np.arange(nx) * dx
    t = np.arange(nt) * dt
        
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(normalize(data).T, cmap="seismic", vmin=-1, vmax=1, aspect="auto", extent=[x[0], x[-1], t[-1], t[0]], interpolation="none")
plt.xlabel("Distance (m)")
plt.ylabel("Time (s)")
    normalize = lambda x: (x - np.mean(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True)) / np.std(x, axis=-1, keepdims=True) with h5py.File(f"data/{filename.split('/')[-1]}", "r") as fp: dx = fp["Acquisition"].attrs["SpatialSamplingInterval"] fs = fp['Acquisition/Raw[0]'].attrs["OutputDataRate"] dt = 1.0 / fs data = fp["Acquisition/Raw[0]/RawData"][...] data = np.gradient(data, axis=-1) / dt nx, nt = data.shape x = np.arange(nx) * dx t = np.arange(nt) * dt plt.figure() plt.imshow(normalize(data).T, cmap="seismic", vmin=-1, vmax=1, aspect="auto", extent=[x[0], x[-1], t[-1], t[0]], interpolation="none") plt.xlabel("Distance (m)") plt.ylabel("Time (s)")

    Notes:

    • The model was trained on data with a channel spacing of 8-10 m, and a sampling rate of 100 Hz. The model will have a reduced performance on data with different channel spacing and sampling rate.
